<h1 class="text-center mb-4" style="color: var(--primary-green);">Sustainable Farming Practices</h1>

<div class="container">
    <p>
        Sustainable farming is essential for preserving our environment, ensuring food security, and improving farm resilience. Here are some key practices:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Organic Farming:</strong> Avoid synthetic chemicals and focus on natural fertilizers and pest control.</li>
        <li><strong>Water Conservation:</strong> Implement drip irrigation, rainwater harvesting, and soil moisture management.</li>
        <li><strong>Soil Health:</strong> Use crop rotation, cover crops, and composting to maintain healthy soil.</li>
        <li><strong>Agroforestry:</strong> Integrate trees into your farming system for shade, windbreaks, and biodiversity.</li>
        <li><strong>Pest Management:</strong> Employ integrated pest management (IPM) techniques to reduce chemical use.</li>
    </ul>

